snippet.textDisplay:
lol @ some of these comments. Do you think nationalizing healthcare makes healthcare costs go away?

Taxation is just forced crowd-funding. Why force it when people are already doing it voluntarily? There is no shortage of charity in America. We are by far the most charitable country in the world.

Do you honestly think costs will go down with the FEDERAL GOVERNMENT in charge? loool I know no one can honestly believe that. The same corrupt ass fucking government that we bitch about constantly being owned by corporations?

Do you remember what happened with Obamacare? Did the health insurance companies have to surrender profits and bring down costs? Not even close. They posted record profits and costs increased because they had government-guaranteed incomes.

People don't get turned away at hospitals. Americans have raised billions for personal medical emergencies. This ridiculous idea that every other American is going bankrupt over medical emergencies is laughable. Poor people don't even pay the hospital bills and the hospital writes them off. I know because I am poor.

Nationalized healthcare is not necessary or beneficial in the United States. If you want nationalized healthcare in America, you need to fix the corrupt federal government first. And we're a long ass way from that. There are plenty of things they could do to improve the healthcare system (like forcing hospitals and insurance companies into transparent pricing and billing) but putting the federal government in charge as overseer and bankroller is the worst choice imaginable.

snippet.textDisplay:
It's messed up that in the wrong conditions, we humans would rather see the pain and suffering of other people, than deal with the brief mental pain of having to change our minds so those people in pain and suffering can be helped. And in so doing help ourselves for when we need it too, and everyone we love and know. But the brief mental pain of admitting you need to change is too much for too many. So we flock to groups which reinforce what we're doing and polices itself against change for the better.

We think we're so smart but we don't realise how so many of our opinions, views, and actions are a result of our context and our social setting. It doesn't help if that context and social setting is focused on chanting that you're the best in the world because you are. Makes admitting change is needed that much harder.

We're all brilliant idiots depending on context.

snippet.textDisplay: There are even Gofundme campaigns just to pay for funeral expenses. I had a friend who had to start one just to help pay for her sister and her son’s funeral (died from a drunk driver driving on the wrong side of the road). Can you imagine your family members spontaneously dying and you have to turn to the internet to avoid going in debt? From birth to death, the system we live in wants to make our existence as profitable as possible.

snippet.textDisplay: The simple fact of the matter is nobody wants to give a stranger money just so they can have fun. snippet.textDisplay: Vote for Bernie Sanders. The only candidate that doesn't change his stance to follow the votes. That our government should put the citizens above the rich donor class and corporations. Don't vote for the candidates that the donors and corporations literally buy to do their bidding... Vote for the only candidate that denies all corporate money and all billionaire donations. We've tried the broken system and it continues to get worse for the middle-class and the working poor, not to mention those in desperate poverty and homeless. It's time to try a new type of candidate, one that actually care for and works for the people. Vote for Bernie!
